 I have no cash atm.  Just give me some ideas of what I could put in the offhand to hold taunt in a fight, or just tell me that the Hammer is a bad idea.<br><br>Thanks much,<br><br>Piledriver Baker<br>54 warrior <br>Tholuxe Paells <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utiejinnie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tiejinnie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/18/02 6:30:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3931.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://homex.coolconnect.com/member3/Tiejinnie/images/Avatar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hammer of Battle</span><hr size=1> It's a sucky hammer.<br><br>While 17dmg is gud, but 25delay in PRIMARY only makes it a white elephant - nice to look at, but that's it.<br><br>If only they made it Off-Hand useable, then this baby would be much sought after. <p><fontcolor="cornflowerblue"><i>Tiejinnie - 60 Warrior<br>Morganna - 57 Cleric<br>Tiejinnie - Lurikeen NightShade<br>Legion of Avatars</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ualdarionshard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aldarion Shard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/18/02 7:16:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3931.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hammer of Battle</span><hr size=1> should be a decent dps item though, no? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dobbofutreet>Dobbo Futreet</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 647<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/18/02 7:58:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3931.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://images.flamingtext.com/clipart/icons/gen/War/Swords/Sword7.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hammer of Battle</span><hr size=1> at low levels but ratio w/ low delay would win because of the dmg bonus. <p>><b><center><font face="bookman old style" SIZE = 2><font color="blue"></br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...num=92644></br> Dobbo Slaysalot</a></br> 53 Halfling Champion</br> <a href=http://www.avidgamers.com/KindredSpirits>Kindred Spirits</a></br> <a href=http://www.tmlog.com>Tarew Marr League of Guilds</a></br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwubaogoldenarmz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wubao Goldenarmz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 157<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/18/02 8:09:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3931.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   don't discount ratio for DPS ...</span><hr size=1> For taunt, a 17 damage, 25 delay weapon might not be the best thing you can equip.<br><br>For DPS, however, it's very good.<br><br>There was a monk parse awhile back that compared the DPS between Jade Mace/Stave of Shielding and Stave of Shielding/Stave of Shielding.<br><br>The SoS/SoS combo won out. I forget the level this was done at, but I believe it was 51 or 54. Something past 50, because the SoS did proc for the person asking.<br><br>Now if a pair of 17/28's can outdamage a 9/18 and a 17/28 ...<br><br>I tend to think a 17/25 mainhand will do a very NICE job when compared to a 9/19 ... in a pure DAMAGE sense.<br><br>People constantly disregard slower weapons with much better ratios. Sometimes that's a bad thing to do.<br><br>And at your level (54) ... I think you can easily snag a Praetor's Blade of Debility (it's a quest out of Sanctus Seru) merely for the proc (very good aggro), until you can save up enough cash for something good like a Frostbringer.<br><br>Just a suggestion though.<br><br>I think when XPing your aggro situation isn't really an issue no matter what you equip. And when raiding, I think there are a LOT of cheap but effective options out there that will allow you to MT at your level, as long as your friends/guildmates are doing their job in regards to aggro.<br><br>Have fun and good luck. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/upiledriverbaker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Piledriver Baker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/19/02 9:25:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3931.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: don't discount ratio for DPS ...</span><hr size=1> Thank you Wubao and others for the informative posts.<br><br>I was kind of thinking that a 17/25 would outdamage a 9/18.  It was just a gut feeling, since the hits looked bigger at it seemed like the monsters fell faster with the hammer in hand.  I wasn't sure what effect my damage bonus would have wielding a faster weapon in my onhand, but like I said, the hammer seemed better.<br><br>Another reason I like the hammer is for the extra hps and stats. It has 10str 5dex 5agi and 75hps.  It is also 0 weight (good for monks).  I am happy knowing that if I get a good offhander (w/ proc) I can hold taunt in a raid situation.<br><br>Piledriver Baker<br>54 warrior<br>Tholuxe Paells <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/upiledriverbaker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Piledriver Baker</A> at: 9/19/02 9:30:31 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhyardgune.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hyardgune</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/19/02 11:21:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3931.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: don't discount ratio for DPS ...</span><hr size=1> An important consideration is also when you are on a raid and are NOT MT, this would be a nice dps weapon that won't draw you much aggro. <p>Hyardgune Varangian <BR> 57 Ogre Myrmidon of Gathered Might</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uscarsoulklaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ScarSoulKlaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 132<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/19/02 12:17:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3931.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: don't discount ratio for DPS ...</span><hr size=1> Another consideration is your haste, and how often you MT.<br><br>If you can get the delay low enough that 17 damage is going to shine through quite nicely.  If you're going to go Defensive a lot you're going to have some problems as long as you don't have a proc weapon regardless of what you're using, so you may as well swing big.<br><br>Remember the key to it all - spend the first 10-15 seconds soloing the mob and build up as much hate as you can.  After that you should be fine with most mobs you'll be facing.<br><br>I'm not using anything fancy for weapons, and I can hold agro fine in a lot of situations just by spending that bit of time to get the mob focused on me.<br><br>Good luck with it.... <p>Scartle SoulKlaw<br>Dwarven Warlord of Forlorn, E'CI Server<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69785">Hard work and patience pay off</a> </p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showNextMessage?topicID=3931.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3931.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.emailToFriend?topicID=3931.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.threadControl?topicID=3931.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3931.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub14.ezboar